---
import { getRelativeLocaleUrl } from "astro:i18n";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Breadcrumb from "@/components/Breadcrumb.astro";
import Main from "@/components/Main.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
import config from "@/config";

const locale = Astro.currentLocale ?? config.site.lang;
---

<Layout
  title={`PRD to Prototype | ${config.site.title}`}
  description="The AI PM workflow for turning product requirements into working prototypes using LLM pair programming — from intent to behavior review to spec refinement."
>
  <Header />
  <Breadcrumb />

  <Main pageTitle="PRD to Prototype" class="app-prose">
    <p class="text-muted-foreground text-lg">
      The AI PM workflow is shifting from "write PRD and wait" to "write PRD,
      generate prototype, test product behavior, then refine spec."
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">
      Why Prototypes Matter More in AI Products
    </h2>
    <p>
      AI products have non-deterministic behavior. A static PRD cannot fully
      capture how a model will reason, what edge cases it will hit, or how users
      will interact with generated output. Prototypes let PMs test behavior
      before committing engineering resources.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-semibold">Workflow</h2>
    <ol class="mt-2 list-inside list-decimal space-y-3">
      <li>
        <strong>Product intent</strong> — Define the user problem and desired outcome.
        Not features — outcomes.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Constraints and non-goals</strong> — What should the system never
        do? What's out of scope for this iteration?
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Interaction flow</strong> — How does the user interact with the AI?
        What's the approval flow? What happens on failure?
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Data assumptions</strong> — What data exists? What's the schema? Where
        are the gaps between available data and what the model needs?
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Prototype generation</strong> — Use LLM pair programming (Claude Code,
        Cursor) to generate a working prototype. Review behavior, not just code.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Behavior review</strong> — Test the prototype against the original
        intent. Does it solve the user problem? Where does it break?
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Spec refinement</strong> — Update the PRD with learnings from the
        prototype. The spec becomes tighter because you've tested behavior.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-semibold">What PMs Should Review</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 space-y-2">
      <li>Does the output match the user's mental model?</li>
      <li>Where does the AI produce surprising or wrong results?</li>
      <li>Is the human-in-the-loop flow clear and frictionless?</li>
      <li>What would break if this shipped to 100x more users?</li>
      <li>What signals would tell you the product is working?</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-semibold">Common Mistakes</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Treating the prototype as production code — it's a thinking tool, not a
        shippable artifact.
      </li>
      <li>
        Reviewing code quality instead of product behavior — PMs should evaluate
        whether the right problem is solved, not whether the code is elegant.
      </li>
      <li>
        Skipping the spec refinement step — the prototype's value is in what it
        teaches you about the requirements.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="border-border mt-8 rounded-lg border p-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Related</h2>
      <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a
          href={getRelativeLocaleUrl(locale, "playbook/ai-native-prd")}
          class="text-accent hover:underline"
        >
          AI-Native PRD
        </a>
        <a
          href={getRelativeLocaleUrl(locale, "playbook/vibe-coding")}
          class="text-accent hover:underline"
        >
          Vibe Coding
        </a>
        <a
          href={getRelativeLocaleUrl(locale, "playbook")}
          class="text-accent hover:underline"
        >
          Playbook Index
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
